ka, the government spokesman, told reporters the two libyans were arrested friday night on their arrival on a flight from cotonou, benin, via abidjan, ivory coast
he said another man he described as a libyan agent carrying false papers had been arrested two days earlier at kadira on the senegal-mali border, where he was trying to enter senegal by train
ka provided no details on the arms and explosives that were seized. he said the investigation was still in progress, and he said more information would be disclosed later this week
presidential and legislative elections are scheduled next sunday in senegal, with president abdel diouf expected to win re-election to a new five-year term
senegal, a nation of 6 million people at the western tip of africa, has close ties to france and generally conservative, pro-western policies
it broke diplomatic relations with libya in 1980, accusing the regime of col. moammar gadhafi of trying to destabilize senegal and other west african nations. relations later improved, and gadhafi visited dakar in december 1985, but formal ties have not been resumed
